node.accessibility_caption: Photo by EARTH in Náousa, Kikladhes, Greece with @minogiannisvalantis. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
A stunning spot for dinner in Greece!🌺 Who’d you like to have dinner with here?😍

📌 Naousa is a village in the Cyclades. It is located in the northeastern corner of the island of Paros, and it has a population of 2,870. In the summer, when it is warm and sunny almost every day, Naousa attracts many tourists from all around Europe because of the climate and the nearby beaches, like Kolympithres.

📍Naousa, Paros, Greece🇬🇷
📽 by @minogiannisvalantis

node.text:
Old Harry Rocks in England!🍰 Have you ever been to England?😍 

📌 Old Harry Rocks can be seen up close on foot by walking from either Studland or Swanage across Ballard Down, a gorgeous chalk grassland that offers spectacular views across the Jurassic Coast.
Further south from Old Harry Rocks along the South West Coast Path is the charming coastal town of Swanage, and beyond that Durlston Country Park and Dancing Ledge.

📍Old Harry Rocks, Dorset, England🇬🇧 
📽 by @luigichiurchi

node.text:
The way to Heaven!⛅️ Who’d you like to walk with here?😍

📌 The First Cliff Walk in Switzerland wraps around the mountains of Grindelwald and is a breathtaking experience for those brave enough to embark on the hike up the Bernese Alps. Most of the area is car free, First included. Grindelwald itself can be reached by car, but for nearly all other places you can travel by train and cable cars only.

Travel Tips: The easiest way to get to First Cliff Walk is by taking a 25-minutes gondola ride from Grindelwald to First. From there, it's just a short walk of 5 minutes to the Cliff Walk. You cannot drive up to First by car or by bus and hiking here from Grindelwald would take you several hours.

📽 by @michelphotographych 
📍First Cliff Walk, Grindelwald, Swiss🇨🇭

node.text:
This is Socotra Island!🌳 Which one is your favorite from 1 - 10?😍 videos by @hobopeeba

📌 Socotra or Soqotra, between the Guardafui Channel and the Arabian Sea, is the largest of the four islands in the Socotra archipelago. The territory is near major shipping routes and is officially part of Yemen, and had long been a subdivision of Aden Governorate.
